reviews.text:
I have to start off saying how much I love this recipe! It’s a very creamy custard with a slight toasted sugar feel with a great caramel and vanilla. I’m a huge fan of the INW custard/brûlée combo which is why I mixed this up to begin with. I let it sit for 3 weeks before busting into this. It’s well worth the wait. &#xD;
&#xD;
Now to explain why only 4 stars for me. In the description you mention the tobacco notes and how they come through. To me, holy grail has little to not tobacco until at about 8%; even then, not very prominent. It’s a weak flavor in my experience. It’s an AMAZING caramel for sure. I was hoping for that RY4 tobacco note to come through possibly, but it didn’t happen. For my taste, I would probably add 2% of TFA RY4 double, or a minute amount of FLV red burley/cured to add the missing tobacco note. &#xD;
&#xD;
No off notes anywhere to be found, just a straight forward, caramel and vanilla custard that tastes amazing.
